A

AbstractScopedPacketChannelComponent - Class in com.github.yona168.giraffe.net.messenger
Provides base Component functionality for objects with AsynchronousChannels and a interface PacketProcessor. On enable, the packetProcessor is enabled, and on disable AbstractScopedPacketChannelComponent.initClose is first ran, coroutineContext is canelled, and finally, AbstractScopedPacketChannelComponent.getSocketChannel is closed.
AbstractScopedPacketChannelComponent(packetProcessor, bufferPool) - Constructor for class com.github.yona168.giraffe.net.messenger.AbstractScopedPacketChannelComponent
Provides base Component functionality for objects with AsynchronousChannels and a interface PacketProcessor. If GClient.Companion.newServerside is used, GClient.getSide is Side.Serverside, and if GClient.Companion.newClientside is used, GClient.getSide is Side.Clientside.

GServer - Class in com.github.yona168.giraffe.net.messenger.server
The given implementation for interface Server. This class uses a MutableMap to store client UUIDs to the interface Client objects, which represent server-side connections. CoroutineScope.coroutineContext is overriden with Dispatchers.IO+AbstractScopedPacketChannelComponent.getJob. After accepting a Client, it writes a handshake packet (see class GClient description), giving it a session UUID as referenced by Client.getSessionUUID. Any interface Client that uses this server should handle the packet accordingly, or ignore it.

Side() - Constructor for enum com.github.yona168.giraffe.net.messenger.client.Companion.Side
The "Side" (client or server) that this client is on. GServer uses GClient objects to process things server side. Thus, a client can have one of two sides. If GClient.Companion.newServerside is used, GClient.getSide is Side.Serverside, and if GClient.Companion.newClientside is used, GClient.getSide is Side.Clientside.
SingleThreadPacketProcessor - Class in com.github.yona168.giraffe.net.messenger.packetprocessor
A interface PacketProcessor that processes all packets on one thread. This is convinient if packets must be processed in a sequential order. Creating an instance of this class is equivalent to creating a class FixedThreadPoolPacketProcessor with a thread amount of 1

write(packet) - Method in class com.github.yona168.giraffe.net.messenger.client.GClient
Launches a coroutine that writes the bytes from a interface SendablePacket to this GClient.getSocketChannel. SendablePacket.build is called to obtain a ByteBuffer, which is then read in its entirety into the channel. The controller ensures that coroutines wait for the preceding one to complete before writing, in order to avoid errors. This process is asynchronous.
